  "text": "Using invertible two-dimensional chaotic maps (CMs) on a square to create symmetric block encryption schemes for visual data has been proposed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] mainly to serve the first purpose, that is, to create encryption schemes with low computational demand. CMs operate in the image domain which means that in some sense bitstream compliance is not an issue, however, they cannot be combined in a straightforward manner with traditional compression techniques.",
